# title: get_data.ipynb
# author: @ericramsey
# description: file used to successfully execute web scrapping for professional athlete statistics

import os
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
from playwright.async_api import async_playwright, TimeoutError as PlaywrightTimeout
import time 

# initialize directories used to store required data
SEASONS = list(range(2016, 2023)) # constant used to create a list for the data in range of NBA Seasons 2016-2024

DATA_DIR = "data"
STANDINGS_DIR = os.path.join(DATA_DIR, "standings") # directory used to store season standings
SCORES_DIR = os.path.join(DATA_DIR, "scores") # directory used to store all game box scores

# (playwright) async function used to obtain html for web scrapping and initiate sleep parameter
# hi babe. titties. love you. 
async def get_html(url, selector, sleep=5, retries=3):
    
    html = None
    
    # initates retries and increases the duration of sleep
    for i in range(1, retries+1): 
        
        time.sleep(sleep * i) # pauses the program for i seconds before attemtping to retrieve data, this avoids being banned from site
        
        try:
            async with async_playwright() as p: # initialize playwright
                
                browser = await p.chromium.launch() # initialize browser
                page = await browser.new_page()
                await page.goto(url) # send new_page() to the url required for data scrape
                print(await page.title()) # display title in output
                html = await page.inner_html(selector) # obtain html
                
        except PlaywrightTimeout:
            
            print(f"Timeout error on {url}") # display timeout error in logs for reference
            continue
            
        else:
            break # web scrapping complete - end loop
            
    return html

# (playwright) async function that passes argument "season" and will scrape the standings data for all games for that season year/number (ex: NBA Season 2016)
async def scrape_season(season):
    
    url = f"https://www.basketball-reference.com/leagues/NBA_{season}_games.html" # sets the seasons to url to retrieve data accuratly.
    html = await get_html(url, "#content .filter")
    
    soup = BeautifulSoup(html)
    links = soup.find_all("a") # locate <a> tags from url containing required data
    standings_pages = [f"https://www.basketball-reference.com{l['href']}" for l in links] # completes the full link or url to complete the data scrapping
    
    # saves the scraped data to disk before processing to ensure accuracy of the retrieved information
    for url in standings_pages:
        
        save_path = os.path.join(STANDINGS_DIR, url.split("/")[-1]) # initiates the path to location of where the data will be saved to be processed later
        
        # statement used to avoid any duplicate saved data
        if os.path.exists(save_path):
            
            continue
            
        html = await get_html(url, "#all_schedule") # retrives the boxscores data table from individual standings
        with open(save_path, "w+") as f:
            
            f.write(html) # writes and saves the data to the file "f"

In [7]:
# (playwright) async function that passes argument "standings_file" and will scrape the boxscore data for all games for that season year/number (ex: NBA Season 2016)
async def scrape_game(standings_file):

    with open(standings_file, 'r') as f:
        
        html = f.read()
        
    soup = BeautifulSoup(html)
    links = soup.find_all("a") # locating all the links in the html table
    hrefs = (l.get('href') for l in links) # removes the html <a> tag and returns just the required link
    box_scores = [f"https://www.basketball-reference.com{l}" for l in hrefs if l and "boxscore" in l and '.html'] # filters the url further, targeting box scores
    
    # saves the scraped data to disk before processing to ensure accuracy of the retrieved information
    for url in box_scores:
        
        save_path = os.path.join(SCORES_DIR, url.split("/")[-1]) # initiates the path to location of where the data will be saved to be processed later
        
        # statement used to avoid any duplicate saved data
        if os.path.exists(save_path):
        
            continue
        
        html = await get_html(url, "#content") # retrives the standings data table from individual standings - selects id: #content
        
        if not html:
            
            continue
            
        with open(save_path, "w+") as f:
            
                  f.write(html) # writes and saves the data to the file "f"

import pandas as pd

# loop used to initiate data scraping and obtain required standiings_files data
import pandas as pd

for season in SEASONS:
    files = [s for s in standings_files if str(season) in s]
    
    for f in files:
        filepath = os.path.join(STANDINGS_DIR, f)
        
        await scrape_game(filepath)
